 The following concepts and implementations are original works by Patrik Fogoš
 (FogyXT), created between June 8-13, 2026 as part of the JARVIS project:

 1. STANDBY NEURON AGENTS (tools/memory_agents.py)
    - Domain-specialized AI agents that sleep on disk (DEEP_SLEEP = 0 RAM, 0 tokens)
    - Sparse activation via trigger pattern matching + centroid similarity
    - Consensus panel voting mechanism for multi-agent retrieval
    - See: knowledge/research/standby-neuron-agents.md

 2. NEUROGENESIS (tools/memory_agents.py: neurogenesis())
    - Automatic spawning of new memory agents from semantic clusters
    - Tag-based and embedding-based domain detection
    - Self-pruning of inactive (DEAD) agents
    - See: knowledge/research/standby-neuron-agents.md

 3. FIVE-TIER BIOLOGICALLY-INSPIRED MEMORY ARCHITECTURE
    - Episodic Buffer (hippocampal analog) with Ebbinghaus decay
    - Semantic Store (neocortical analog) with hybrid dense+BM25 search
    - Knowledge Graph (association cortex analog) with entity extraction
    - Cold Archive (distributed cortex analog) with thaw capability
    - Sleep-like consolidation pipeline with DeepSeek LLM integration
    - See: knowledge/decisions/five-tier-memory-for-jarvis.md

 4. EBBIHHAUS FORGETTING CURVE FOR EPISODIC AI MEMORY (tools/episodic_memory.py)
    - Mathematical implementation: score(t) = n_accesses^beta * exp(-lambda * delta_t) * importance
    - Forget (0.05) and Promote (0.65) thresholds
    - Access-based reinforcement with working→episodic overflow

